.TH "task_cgroup_path" 9 "task_cgroup_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
task_cgroup_path \- cgroup path of a task in the first cgroup hierarchy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" task_cgroup_path
.BI "(struct task_struct *task "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t buflen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "task" 12
target task
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer to write the path into
.IP "buflen" 12
the length of the buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determine \fItask\fP's cgroup on the first (the one with the lowest non-zero
hierarchy_id) cgroup hierarchy and copy its path into \fIbuf\fP.  This
function grabs cgroup_mutex and shouldn't be used inside locks used by
cgroup controller callbacks.

Return value is the same as \fBkernfs_path\fP.
